The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for automatic database administration, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the application of deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of advisory tools for database configuration, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the physical layout of the database store, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
